

=Bio=

"I have a formal education in Political Science and Peace Studies.

I have also learned a lot working and living with other human beings, living with my wife and daughter, and getting to know myself.

My basic attitude towards life and work is one of openness and exploration.
Something I am proud of is having helped persons to find their voice and nurture their talents.
I cultivate the attitude that each person possess inherent beauty. I have never worked with groups which were uninteresting and unwise.

My wish is to contribute to world peace and ecological balance while remaining firmly rooted in the town and country I live.


Specialties:Conflict Resolution / Transformation, in theory and practice.
Interpersonal and Community mediation."

